						<figure class="thumb tright show-info-icon" style="width: 240px"> 	<a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20210603015015/https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/essentialsdocs/images/c/c4/Region.png/revision/latest?cb=20190822193258" class="image"><img alt="" src="https://web.archive.org/web/20210603015015im_/https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/essentialsdocs/images/c/c4/Region.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/240?cb=20190822193258" decoding="async" width="240" height="160" class="thumbimage" data-image-name="Region.png" data-image-key="Region.png"></a> 	 	<figcaption class="thumbcaption"> 		 			<a href="/web/20210603015015/https://essentialsdocs.fandom.com/wiki/File:Region.png" class="info-icon"><svg><use xlink:href="#wds-icons-info-small"></use></svg></a> 		 		 		 			<p class="caption">The Essen region map.</p> 		 	</figcaption> </figure>
						<p>
							The&nbsp;<b>region map</b>&nbsp;(also known as the&nbsp;<b>Town Map</b>) is the picture that shows the entire region. This page describes how to set up a region map.
						</p><p>
							It should not be confused with a&nbsp;<a href="/web/20210603015015/https://essentialsdocs.fandom.com/wiki/Maps" title="Maps">game map</a>&nbsp;- those are the overworld areas the player walks around in, each of which typically depicts a single town or route, and are often&nbsp;<a href="/web/20210603015015/https://essentialsdocs.fandom.com/wiki/Connecting_maps" title="Connecting maps">linked together</a>.
						</p>
